1. cs.LG (Machine Learning): The paper introduces a method for computing the influence of a training example on a prediction made by a model during the training process. This is a core topic in machine learning and falls under the sub-category of cs.LG. 
2. cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition): The paper applies the proposed method on vision tasks and discusses insights from the experiments. This suggests that the paper is related to computer vision and falls under the sub-category of cs.CV. 
3. cs.CL (Computation and Language): The paper also applies the proposed method on natural language tasks and discusses insights from the experiments. This suggests that the paper is related to natural language processing and falls under the sub-category of cs.CL. 
4. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence): The paper proposes a method for estimating the influence of training data on a model's prediction, which is a core topic in artificial intelligence. This suggests that the paper falls under the sub-category of cs.AI. 
5. cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms): The paper discusses the implementation of the proposed method, which involves using random projections and saved checkpoints. This suggests that the paper is related to data structures and algorithms and falls under the sub-category of cs.DS.
